    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Historical Jesus</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Joan Ogden letter disputes statement in April 23 review of Thomas Kahill's book Desire of the Everlasting Hills that there is no evidence outside Bible to support existence of Jesus</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The review of Thomas Cahill's ''Desire of the Everlasting Hills'' (April 23) states, ''There is not a shred of historical evidence outside the Bible itself to support the existence of Jesus.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The review of Thomas Cahill's ''Desire of the Everlasting Hills'' (April 23) states, ''There is not a shred of historical evidence outside the Bible itself to support the existence of Jesus.''</p>
        <p>There are actually three very definite ''shreds'': in ''Antiquities,'' by the Roman (Jewish) historian Josephus; in the ''Annals'' of Tacitus (another Roman historian); and in ''The Passing of Peregrinus,'' by Lucian of Samosata, a satirist.</p>
        <p>Joan Ogden  New York</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
